{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01VkKyukYdk9VDJUiyY4kC6P","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→# Session Issues Log — 2026-03-21\n     2→\n     3→### 0-1-sprint-state-live-updates — verify (2026-03-21T07:55Z)\n     4→\n     5→- **Bug found and fixed:** `parseRalphStatus()` in `migration.ts` was missing the new `currentStory`, `currentPhase`, `lastAction`, `acProgress` fields added by this story. Migration test was failing. Fixed by adding null defaults to the return object.\n     6→- **Observability gap:** VictoriaLogs returned zero log events for all `codeharness progress` CLI invocations. The progress command doesn't emit structured logs.\n     7→\n     8→### 0-2-ralph-progress-display — verify (2026-03-21T08:00Z)\n     9→\n    10→- **Proof format issue:** AC3 initially reused evidence from AC2 without its own `bash` code block, causing `codeharness verify` to report 3/4 ACs. Fixed by adding a distinct bash block.\n    11→- **No BATS tests in container:** `ralph/tests/` not included in npm package. Verification relied on direct function invocation with mock data.\n    12→- **VictoriaLogs query syntax:** `_stream_id:*` pattern invalid for VictoriaLogs. Used `*` wildcard instead.\n    13→\n    14→### 0-3-run-command-dashboard — verify (2026-03-21T08:04Z)\n    15→\n    16→- **Minor format deviations:** Story specified checkmark/cross prefixes but implementation uses `[OK]`/`[FAIL]` tags. Functionally equivalent, passed verification.\n    17→- **Architecture difference:** Story specified `DashboardFormatter` class but implementation uses Ink React components. Same functionality, different design.\n    18→\n    19→### 0-5-1-stream-json-claude-driver — verify (2026-03-21T08:09Z)\n    20→\n    21→- Clean verification — all 4 ACs passed without issues.\n    22→"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"14bb9049-f41e-41a8-aff7-919131cd9a0b","uuid":"d7d99492-a6c3-46ce-bd2f-99ce63a69b66","timestamp":"2026-03-21T10:29:49.824Z","tool_use_result":{"type":"text","file":{"filePath":"/Users/ivintik/dev/personal/codeharness/_bmad-output/implementation-artifacts/.session-issues.md","content":"# Session Issues Log — 2026-03-21\n\n### 0-1-sprint-state-live-updates — verify (2026-03-21T07:55Z)\n\n- **Bug found and fixed:** `parseRalphStatus()` in `migration.ts` was missing the new `currentStory`, `currentPhase`, `lastAction`, `acProgress` fields added by this story. Migration test was failing. Fixed by adding null defaults to the return object.\n- **Observability gap:** VictoriaLogs returned zero log events for all `codeharness progress` CLI invocations. The progress command doesn't emit structured logs.\n\n### 0-2-ralph-progress-display — verify (2026-03-21T08:00Z)\n\n- **Proof format issue:** AC3 initially reused evidence from AC2 without its own `bash` code block, causing `codeharness verify` to report 3/4 ACs. Fixed by adding a distinct bash block.\n- **No BATS tests in container:** `ralph/tests/` not included in npm package. Verification relied on direct function invocation with mock data.\n- **VictoriaLogs query syntax:** `_stream_id:*` pattern invalid for VictoriaLogs. Used `*` wildcard instead.\n\n### 0-3-run-command-dashboard — verify (2026-03-21T08:04Z)\n\n- **Minor format deviations:** Story specified checkmark/cross prefixes but implementation uses `[OK]`/`[FAIL]` tags. Functionally equivalent, passed verification.\n- **Architecture difference:** Story specified `DashboardFormatter` class but implementation uses Ink React components. Same functionality, different design.\n\n### 0-5-1-stream-json-claude-driver — verify (2026-03-21T08:09Z)\n\n- Clean verification — all 4 ACs passed without issues.\n","numLines":22,"startLine":1,"totalLines":22}}}
