{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"type":"text","text":"You are a black-box verifier. Your job is to verify that a software feature works correctly from the user's perspective — using ONLY the installed CLI, documentation, and observability data. You have NO access to source code.\n\n## Why Black-Box Verification\n\nThis workspace contains NO source code. The `src/` directory does not exist. This is intentional — you must verify the feature works as a user would experience it, not by reading implementation details.\n\n## Step 1: Read README.md\n\nStart by reading `README.md` in the workspace at `/tmp/codeharness-verify-0-5-2-stream-event-parser/README.md`.\n\n## Step 2: Review Acceptance Criteria\n\nThe story file `story.md` at `/tmp/codeharness-verify-0-5-2-stream-event-parser/story.md` contains the acceptance criteria. Here they are:\n\n1. **Given** `content_block_start` with `tool_use`, **When** parsed, **Then** emits `{ type: 'tool-start', name: 'Bash', id: 'toolu_xxx' }`.\n2. **Given** `content_block_delta` with `input_json_delta`, **When** parsed, **Then** accumulates tool input and emits `{ type: 'tool-input', partial: '...' }`.\n3. **Given** `content_block_stop` after a tool, **When** parsed, **Then** emits `{ type: 'tool-complete' }`.\n4. **Given** `content_block_delta` with `text_delta`, **When** parsed, **Then** emits `{ type: 'text', text: '...' }`.\n5. **Given** `system/api_retry`, **When** parsed, **Then** emits `{ type: 'retry', attempt: N, delay: ms }`.\n6. **Given** `result` event, **When** parsed, **Then** emits `{ type: 'result', cost: N, sessionId: '...' }`.\n\n## Step 3: Verify Each AC\n\nFor EACH acceptance criterion, run commands inside the Docker container `codeharness-verify` using `docker exec`.\n\nThe `parseStreamLine` function is exported from the codeharness package. To access it inside the container:\n\n```bash\ndocker exec codeharness-verify sh -c 'VITEST=1 node --input-type=module -e \"\nimport { parseStreamLine } from \\\"/usr/local/lib/node_modules/codeharness/dist/index.js\\\";\n// Test code here\nconst result = parseStreamLine(JSON.stringify({...}));\nconsole.log(JSON.stringify(result));\n\"'\n```\n\nFor each AC, construct the appropriate NDJSON input and verify the output matches the expected event structure.\n\n### AC1: content_block_start with tool_use\nInput: `{\"type\":\"stream_event\",\"event\":{\"type\":\"content_block_start\",\"content_block\":{\"type\":\"tool_use\",\"name\":\"Bash\",\"id\":\"toolu_xxx\"}}}`\nExpected output: `{\"type\":\"tool-start\",\"name\":\"Bash\",\"id\":\"toolu_xxx\"}`\n\n### AC2: content_block_delta with input_json_delta\nInput: `{\"type\":\"stream_event\",\"event\":{\"type\":\"content_block_delta\",\"delta\":{\"type\":\"input_json_delta\",\"partial_json\":\"hello\"}}}`\nExpected output: `{\"type\":\"tool-input\",\"partial\":\"hello\"}`\n\n### AC3: content_block_stop\nInput: `{\"type\":\"stream_event\",\"event\":{\"type\":\"content_block_stop\"}}`\nExpected output: `{\"type\":\"tool-complete\"}`\n\n### AC4: content_block_delta with text_delta\nInput: `{\"type\":\"stream_event\",\"event\":{\"type\":\"content_block_delta\",\"delta\":{\"type\":\"text_delta\",\"text\":\"Hello world\"}}}`\nExpected output: `{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"Hello world\"}`\n\n### AC5: system/api_retry\nInput: `{\"type\":\"system\",\"subtype\":\"api_retry\",\"attempt\":2,\"retry_delay_ms\":5000}`\nExpected output: `{\"type\":\"retry\",\"attempt\":2,\"delay\":5000}`\n\n### AC6: result event\nInput: `{\"type\":\"result\",\"cost_usd\":0.05,\"session_id\":\"sess_123\"}`\nExpected output: `{\"type\":\"result\",\"cost\":0.05,\"sessionId\":\"sess_123\"}`\n\n### Observability Endpoints\n\nQuery these from the HOST (not inside the container) for runtime evidence:\n\n- **VictoriaLogs** (logs): `http://localhost:9428`\n  - Example: `curl 'http://localhost:9428/select/logsql/query?query=_stream_id:*&limit=10'`\n\nAfter EACH `docker exec` command, query:\n```bash\ncurl 'http://localhost:9428/select/logsql/query?query=_stream_id:*&start=-30s&limit=100'\n```\nIf zero log entries, note: `[OBSERVABILITY GAP] No log events detected for this user interaction`\n\n## Step 4: Write Proof Document\n\nWrite your verification proof to: `/tmp/codeharness-verify-0-5-2-stream-event-parser/verification/0-5-2-stream-event-parser-proof.md`\n\nUse this format for each AC:\n\n```markdown\n## AC N: description\n\n```bash\ndocker exec codeharness-verify ...\n```\n\n```output\n<actual output>\n```\n```\n\n**IMPORTANT: Only use `bash` and `output` as code fence languages.** Never use bare ``` fences without a language tag.\n\n## Critical Rules\n\n1. **ALL commands MUST use `docker exec codeharness-verify ...`** — do NOT run commands directly on the host filesystem.\n2. **Do NOT attempt to access source code** — there is no `src/` directory.\n3. **Report REAL failures** — do NOT fabricate passing evidence.\n4. **Every AC needs functional evidence** — reading docs alone is not evidence.\n5. **[ESCALATE] is ONLY for things genuinely impossible to automate** — physical hardware, paid external services, etc. Infrastructure problems are FAIL, not ESCALATE.\n\nMANDATORY — End your response with a `## Session Issues` section."}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_01Mp5dqJX6NKNz3na3sHmnxY","session_id":"14bb9049-f41e-41a8-aff7-919131cd9a0b","uuid":"0dcb4401-5e5d-4b53-9322-59073fd53a0f","timestamp":"2026-03-21T10:33:35.424Z"}
